## **Description**
The **Filter **operator allows to filter input data using a boolean expression, defined in the configuration settings.

## **Input**
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**node**

Any

The input data that you want to filter

**in0**

Any

The input data that you want to use in the boolean expression

**in…**

Any

N-th input node containing the data that you want to use in the boolean expression

> Warning

Data types linked to **in… **inputs must correspond to data types allowed in the particular expression.

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**out0**

Any

If the boolean expression is true, the operator returns the filtered input node.

If the boolean expression is false, the operator returns an empty string.

## **Settings**
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Inputs **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an input node to the list.

- In the **Condition **section, enter the boolean expression that you want to use.

> Note

The available boolean operators are:

**AND **

- **OR **

- **NOT**

- **&gt;=**

- **&lt;=**

- **&gt;**

- **&lt;**

- **=**

- **)**

- **(**

- **!=**

- In the **Produce when **section, select "True" (or "False") to return the input node value if the boolean expression is true (or, respectively, false).

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

> Tip

To rename an input node, click on its name to edit it.

To remove an input node from the list, move your mouse over it and click ![](data:image/png;base64,) in the **Action **column; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## **Special cases**
In special cases, the operator behaves as follows:

**Case**

**Behavior**

**NULL input node (no input node)**

The operator does not perform any operation. The system logs a warning event.

**NULL input condition (no input condition)**

T he operator considers a NULL input as an empty string. The system logs a warning event.
